  "prompt": "What is the best comeback when someone says \"Been there, done that\"?",
  "response": "When someone says \"Been there, done that,\" a good comeback can keep the conversation engaging and light-hearted. Here are a few options you might consider:\n\n1. **\"True, but there's always a new twist!\"**\n   - *Acknowledges their experience while suggesting there's more to explore.*\n\n2. **\"Fair enough! What's next on your list?\"**\n   - *Opens the door for them to share new experiences or plans.*\n\n3. **\"I hear you! Still, some things are worth revisiting.\"**\n   - *Shows understanding and offers a different perspective.*\n\n4. **\"Glad you've got so much experience! Any tips?\"**\n   - *Transforms the statement into a positive interaction by seeking their advice.*\n\n5. **\"Haha, maybe, but some things are just too good to miss again!\"**\n   - *Adds humor while expressing that certain things are still worth doing.*\n\nChoose a response that fits the tone of the conversation and your relationship with the person. The goal is to keep things friendly and possibly steer the dialogue toward new or shared interests.",
